<td>Use generic text: "click here"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Include the target keyword naturally</td>
<td>Stuff multiple keywords: "best internal linking SEO strategy guide 2026"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Keep it concise: 2-5 words</td>
<td>Write full sentences as anchor text</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Vary slightly across pages</td>
<td>Use identical text on every single page</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Match the anchor to the destination content</td>
<td>Mislead with unrelated anchor text</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p><strong>One important nuance:</strong> the Zyppy study also found that sites with very high anchor text variation sometimes saw traffic drops. The counterintuitive takeaway is that consistency in your anchor text may help more than variety.</p>
<p>Use your target keyword as the primary anchor. Vary it slightly ("internal linking guide" vs. "internal linking strategy" vs. "internal link strategy") but do not force completely different phrases every time.</p>
